{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idf3ac1a28-d790-11f0-9f07-ba4fc64746bc","identifier":"/us/usc/t35/s10"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"10"},"text":"§ 10.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Publications","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idf3ac1a29-d790-11f0-9f07-ba4fc64746bc","identifier":"/us/usc/t35/s10/a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"a"},"text":"(a)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The Director may publish in printed, typewritten, or electronic form, the following:","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{"role":"listItem"},"text":"1. Patents and published applications for patents, including specifications and drawings, together with copies of the same. The Patent and Trademark Office may print the headings of the drawings for patents for the purpose of photolithography.","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{"role":"listItem"},"text":"2. Certificates of trade-mark registrations, including statements and drawings, together with copies of the same.","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"3. The Official Gazette of the United States Patent and Trademark Office.","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"4. Annual indexes of patents and patentees, and of trade-marks and registrants.","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"5. Annual volumes of decisions in patent and trade-mark cases.","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"6. Pamphlet copies of the patent laws and rules of practice, laws and rules relating to trade-marks, and circulars or other publications relating to the business of the Office.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"subsection","attrib":{"id":"idf3ac1a2a-d790-11f0-9f07-ba4fc64746bc","identifier":"/us/usc/t35/s10/b"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"b"},"text":"(b)","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":" The Director may exchange any of the publications specified in items 3, 4, 5, and 6 of subsection (a) of this section for publications desirable for the use of the Patent and Trademark Office.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idf3ac1a2b-d790-11f0-9f07-ba4fc64746bc"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1952-07-19/ch950"},"text":"July 19, 1952, ch. 950","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/66/794"},"text":"66 Stat. 794","children":[],"tail":", § 11; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/93/596/s1"},"text":"Pub. L. 93–596, § 1","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1975-01-02"},"text":"Jan. 2, 1975","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/88/1949"},"text":"88 Stat. 1949","children":[],"tail":"; renumbered § 10 and amended "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/106/113/dB/s1000/a/9/tIV/s4507/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 106–113, div. B, § 1000(a)(9) [title IV, §§ 4507(1), 4717(1), 4732(a)(10)(A), 4804(b)]","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1999-11-29"},"text":"Nov. 29, 1999","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/113/1536"},"text":"113 Stat. 1536","children":[],"tail":", 1501A–565, 1501A–580, 1501A–582, 1501A–589; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/107/273/dC/tIII"},"text":"Pub. L. 107–273, div. C, title III","children":[],"tail":", §§ 13205(2)(A), 13206(b)(1)(B), (3)(A), "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2002-11-02"},"text":"Nov. 2, 2002","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/116/1903"},"text":"116 Stat. 1903","children":[],"tail":", 1906.)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"idf3ac1a2c-d790-11f0-9f07-ba4fc64746bc"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"historicalAndRevision","id":"idf3ac1a2d-d790-11f0-9f07-ba4fc64746bc"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Historical and Revision Notes","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Based on Title 35, U.S.C., 1946 ed., §§ 13 and 16 (R.S. 489; ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1947-07-09/ch211/s301"},"text":"July 9, 1947, ch. 211, § 301","children":[],"tail":" (part), "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/61/299"},"text":"61 Stat. 299","children":[],"tail":", repeated in prior and subsequent appropriation acts)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Section is amplified to list the publications of the Patent Office, based on 44 U.S.C., 1946 ed., §§ 283, 283a.","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The second sentence of item 1 of the revised section is a provision appearing annually in appropriation acts to enable the Patent Office to maintain a small printing press to place headings on drawings before the drawings are reproduced.","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Language is changed.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idf3ac1a2e-d790-11f0-9f07-ba4fc64746bc"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"priorProvisions","id":"idf3ac1a2f-d790-11f0-9f07-ba4fc64746bc"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Prior Provisions","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"A prior section 10 was renumbered ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t35/s9"},"text":"section 9 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"idf3ac1a30-d790-11f0-9f07-ba4fc64746bc"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2002—Subsec. (a). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/107/273/s13206/b/3/A"},"text":"Pub. L. 107–273, § 13206(b)(3)(A)","children":[],"tail":", amended directory language of "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/106/113/s1000/a/9/tIV/s4804/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 106–113, § 1000(a)(9) [title IV, § 4804(b)]","children":[],"tail":". See 1999 Amendment note below."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (a)1. ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/107/273/s13205/2/A"},"text":"Pub. L. 107–273, § 13205(2)(A)","children":[],"tail":", made technical correction to directory language of "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/106/113/s1000/a/9/tIV/s4507/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 106–113, § 1000(a)(9) [title IV, § 4507(1)]","children":[],"tail":". See 1999 Amendment note below."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (b). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/107/273/s13206/b/1/B"},"text":"Pub. L. 107–273, § 13206(b)(1)(B)","children":[],"tail":", made technical correction to directory language of "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/106/113/s1000/a/9/tIV/s4732/a/10/A"},"text":"Pub. L. 106–113, § 1000(a)(9) [title IV, § 4732(a)(10)(A)]","children":[],"tail":". See 1999 Amendment note below."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1999—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/106/113/s1000/a/9/tIV/s4717/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 106–113, § 1000(a)(9) [title IV, § 4717(1)]","children":[],"tail":", renumbered "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t35/s11"},"text":"section 11 of this title","children":[],"tail":" as this section."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (a). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/106/113/s1000/a/9/tIV/s4804/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 106–113, § 1000(a)(9) [title IV, § 4804(b)]","children":[],"tail":", as amended by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/107/273/s13206/b/3/A"},"text":"Pub. L. 107–273, § 13206(b)(3)(A)","children":[],"tail":", which directed the general amendment of the introductory provisions of subsec. (a) of "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t35/s10"},"text":"section 10 of this title","children":[],"tail":" to read “The Director may publish in printed, typewritten, or electronic form, the following:”, was executed to this section, which was "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t35/s11"},"text":"section 11 of this title","children":[],"tail":", to reflect the probable intent of Congress. This section was subsequently renumbered "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t35/s10"},"text":"section 10 of this title","children":[],"tail":" by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/106/113/s1000/a/9/tIV/s4717/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 106–113, § 1000(a)(9) [title IV, § 4717(1)]","children":[],"tail":". Prior to amendment, introductory provisions of subsec. (a) read as follows: “The Commissioner may print, or cause to be printed, the following:”. See note above and Effective Date of 1999 Amendment note below."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (a)1. ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/106/113/s1000/a/9/tIV/s4507/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 106–113, § 1000(a)(9) [title IV, § 4507(1)]","children":[],"tail":", as amended by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/107/273/s13205/2/A"},"text":"Pub. L. 107–273, § 13205(2)(A)","children":[],"tail":", inserted “and published applications for patents” after “Patents”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (b). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/106/113/s1000/a/9/tIV/s4732/a/10/A"},"text":"Pub. L. 106–113, § 1000(a)(9) [title IV, § 4732(a)(10)(A)]","children":[],"tail":", as amended by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/107/273/s13206/b/1/B"},"text":"Pub. L. 107–273, § 13206(b)(1)(B)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “Director” for “Commissioner”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1975—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/93/596"},"text":"Pub. L. 93–596","children":[],"tail":" substituted “Patent and Trademark Office” for “Patent Office”, wherever appearing."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"idf3ac1a31-d790-11f0-9f07-ba4fc64746bc"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDateOfAmendment","id":"idf3ac1a32-d790-11f0-9f07-ba4fc64746bc"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date of 1999 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/106/113/dB/s1000/a/9/tIV/s4508"},"text":"Pub. L. 106–113, div. B, § 1000(a)(9) [title IV, § 4508]","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1999-11-29"},"text":"Nov. 29, 1999","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/113/1536"},"text":"113 Stat. 1536","children":[],"tail":", 1501A–566, as amended by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/107/273/dC/tIII/s13205/3"},"text":"Pub. L. 107–273, div. C, title III, § 13205(3)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2002-11-02"},"text":"Nov. 2, 2002","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/116/1903"},"text":"116 Stat. 1903","children":[],"tail":", provided that: "},{"tag":"quotedContent","attrib":{"origin":"/us/pl/107/273/dC/tIII/s13205/3"},"text":"“Except as otherwise provided in this section, sections 4502 through 4504 and 4506 through 4507 [amending sections 10 to 12, 119, 120, 122, 135, 154, 181, 252, 284, and 374 of this title and enacting provisions set out as notes under sections 41 and 122 of this title], and the amendments made by such sections, shall be effective as of ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2000-11-29"},"text":"November 29, 2000","children":[],"tail":", and shall apply only to applications (including international applications designating the United States) filed on or after that date. The amendments made by section 4504 [amending "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t35/s154"},"text":"section 154 of this title","children":[],"tail":"] shall additionally apply to any pending application filed before "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2000-11-29"},"text":"November 29, 2000","children":[],"tail":", if such pending application is published pursuant to a request of the applicant under such procedures as may be established by the Director. Except as otherwise provided in this section, the amendments made by section 4505 [amending "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t35/s102"},"text":"section 102 of this title","children":[],"tail":"] shall be effective as of "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2000-11-29"},"text":"November 29, 2000","children":[],"tail":" and shall apply to all patents and all applications for patents pending on or filed after "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2000-11-29"},"text":"November 29, 2000","children":[],"tail":". Patents resulting from an international application filed before "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2000-11-29"},"text":"November 29, 2000","children":[],"tail":" and applications published pursuant to section 122(b) [probably means "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t35/s122/b"},"text":"section 122(b) of title 35","children":[],"tail":"] or Article 21(2) of the treaty defined in section 351(a) [probably means "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t35/s351/a"},"text":"section 351(a) of title 35","children":[],"tail":"] resulting from an international application filed before "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2000-11-29"},"text":"November 29, 2000","children":[],"tail":" shall not be effective as prior art as of the filing date of the international application; however, such patents shall be effective as prior art in accordance with section 102(e) in effect on "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"2000-11-28"},"text":"November 28, 2000","children":[],"tail":".”"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Amendment by section 1000(a)(9) [title IV, §§ 4717(1), 4732(a)(10)(A)] of ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/106/113"},"text":"Pub. L. 106–113","children":[],"tail":" effective 4 months after "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1999-11-29"},"text":"Nov. 29, 1999","children":[],"tail":", see section 1000(a)(9) [title IV, § 4731] of "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/106/113"},"text":"Pub. L. 106–113","children":[],"tail":", set out as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t35/s1"},"text":"section 1 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"effectiveDateOfAmendment","id":"idf3ac1a33-d790-11f0-9f07-ba4fc64746bc"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Effective Date of 1975 Amendment","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Amendment by ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/93/596"},"text":"Pub. L. 93–596","children":[],"tail":" effective "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1975-01-02"},"text":"Jan. 2, 1975","children":[],"tail":", see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/93/596/s4"},"text":"section 4 of Pub. L. 93–596","children":[],"tail":", set out as a note under "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t15/s1111"},"text":"section 1111 of Title 15","children":[],"tail":", Commerce and Trade."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
